[{"type":"{{","value":[["pagebanner"],["S-amer africa default banner.jpg"]]},"\nThe ",{"type":"'''","value":["Cuyo"]}," is a region in the west of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Argentina"]]}," bordered in the north and northeast by the ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Andean Northwest (Argentina)"],["Andean Northwest"]]}," region, in the east and southeast by the ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Pampas"]]}," region, in the south by the ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Patagonia (Argentina)"],["Patagonia"]]}," region, and in the west by ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Chile"]]},".\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Regions"]},"\n\nThe following provinces are considered part of the Cuyo:\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Mendoza (province)"],["Mendoza"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["San Juan (province, Argentina)"],["San Juan"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["San Luis (province, Argentina)"],["San Luis"]]}]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Cities"]},"\n\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Mendoza"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["San Juan (city, Argentina)"],["San Juan"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["San José de Jáchal"]]}]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Other destinations"]},"\n\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Ischigualasto Provincial Park"]]}," - ",{"type":"[[","value":[["UNESCO"]]}," site"]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Valle Fértil"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Talampaya National Park"]]}," - ",{"type":"[[","value":[["UNESCO"]]}," site"]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Cerro Aconcagua"]]}]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Understand"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Talk"]},"\n\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get in"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get around"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["See"]},"\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["Itineraries"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Do"]},"\nLearn Spanish in the city of Mendoza to appreciate the culture more. \n\nAs with many places in Argentina, there are a variety of Spanish courses and private lessons are available. There are two extablished language schools, both disorganized but fun, in Mendoza: ",{"type":"'''","value":["Intercultural"]}," , has a range of afternoon activities especailly appropriate for young partiers, and is slightly more expensive; ",{"type":"'''","value":["Greenfields"]}," (aka COINED, after the web bookers) is smaller and feels even less well organised, but many of the teachers work at both schools.\n\nAnother great option for individual or very small tailor-made quality group lessons with a highly trained instructor: ",{"type":"'''","value":["Spanish in Mendoza, Argentina"]}," ",{"type":"'''","value":["(SIMA)"]}," ",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/spanishinmendozaargentina.greenash.net.au\/"]},". This is a better option for those seriously interested in learning or improving their Spanish, although the classes are very enjoyable.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Eat"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Drink"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Stay safe"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Go next"]},"\n\n\n",{"type":"{{","value":[["IsPartOf"],["Argentina"]]},"\n",{"type":"{{","value":[["outlineregion"]]},"\n",{"type":"{{","value":[["geo"],["-32.90726"],["-68.06030"],["zoom=7"]]},"\n\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["WikiPedia:Cuyo (Argentina)"]]}]